<p>UN climate talks in Belém, Brazil, ran past their deadline amid a standoff over whether to include fossil fuel phaseout language in the final text [aljazeera.com#1][france24.com#1][mercopress.com#1]. A draft that dropped any mention of fossil fuels drew an EU rejection, and several delegations accused oil producers including Saudi Arabia and Russia of blocking stronger language [euronews.com#1][japantoday.com#1][ft.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][newarab.com#1][firstpost.com#1]. Host officials urged unity and said they still aim for consensus as talks continue into overtime [michaelwest.com.au#1][mercopress.com#2].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/BywkJZHc7oLr6ReXTK4UJJRVWZvZyBsH5ny3bvKXf1EmhyVxHvKddGe8tgn0w33PbVJtxE1HA3vPf05ZtlcvFtqVF51neUM_29x-9ejrJqRW_CDgxsJin7xeqYnR8JiPiBBhBdAunQCeFycqgJKhrefqBinD3DTcifaXcRIFTaHknA53UlE9TP4lJeyA7WkwGoLDVHWxj8FnLyFPhwLV_inInrG_T53Z13J6MZBga0EaDMlBM3Rr5im7DzrTDaaqWprD7dIoRz_--ia6l_OSLKW7G1FoK9P1xcRFdC_QR7f648FSqe56EOyKA9sIVx1cWOiiw1B1vzZ3ShVOj9y69i-Ojhi9GSDEfQsO5buRhc1f8DX3aXtVfVs0QICPUCdV44H8_oQycPlSmJeJwZq0h8okRft1MSM7ZTa1BNbwEebB6HPOdxuUb4y03H_RbdYIdftbnAQTVUPlgc6JRkT8Gb-1ikOg' alt='Delegates confer as COP30 negotiations enter overtime in Belém.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Core dispute: Brazil’s latest draft dropped prior options on fossil fuel language that many major producers had called unacceptable, while about 80 governments had supported those options [michaelwest.com.au#1]</li><li>EU stance: The European Union rejected the new draft deal as too weak and demanded stronger climate commitments and fossil fuel discussions [euronews.com#1][japantoday.com#1]</li><li>Named opposition: European officials cited Saudi Arabia, Russia and India among those resisting a reference to a fossil fuel phaseout [ft.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]</li><li>Finance tensions: Beyond fossil language, delegates are also split over climate finance as they try to finalize the “Belém Package” [ft.com#1][mercopress.com#1]</li><li>Overtime push: Talks pushed past the scheduled Friday night close, with sessions expected into early Saturday, while the COP30 presidency publicly appealed for unity and consensus [mercopress.com#1][michaelwest.com.au#1]</li><li>Negotiator warning: Panama’s negotiator cautioned that omitting fossil fuels risks turning the talks into a “clown show” [michaelwest.com.au#1]</li></ul><blockquote>Failing to name the causes of the climate crisis is not compromise. It is denial - Juan Carlos Monterrey (Panama negotiator)</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>European Union: The EU rejected the new draft and is pushing to restore strong fossil fuel language and higher overall ambition [euronews.com#1][japantoday.com#1] (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/11/22/pushback-against-phaseout-of-fossil-fuels-upsets-cop30-climate-talks-as-eu-rejects-draft-d'>Euronews; Japan Today</a>)</li><li>Saudi Arabia and Russia: Oil producers led by Saudi Arabia and Russia have pushed back against including a fossil fuel phaseout in the agreement [ft.com#1] (<a href='https://www.ft.com/content/2664a834-54fc-4b41-bd8f-8c5d59f1ad30'>Financial Times</a>)</li><li>France (Ecological Transition Ministry): France’s minister said Russia, Saudi Arabia and India were among those blocking a deal on fossil fuels [straitstimes.com#1] (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/cop30-climate-deal-under-threat-as-nations-clash-over-fossil-fuels'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>COP30 presidency (Brazil): Brazil urged delegates to find unity and consensus to land a deal [michaelwest.com.au#1][mercopress.com#2] (<a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2025/11/21/cop30-chairman-calls-for-consensus-extension-due-to-fire-not-unlikely'>Michael West; MercoPress</a>)</li><li>Panama delegation: Panama warned that failing to name fossil fuels would undermine the credibility of the talks [michaelwest.com.au#1] (<a href='https://michaelwest.com.au/cop30-host-urges-unity-ahead-of-fossil-fuels-showdown/'>Michael West</a>)</li></ul><h